:"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"My current thinking is to add `layers` to `Material` and use that instead.","created_at":"2017-05-30T23:45:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11083#issuecomment-305040163","id":305040163,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11083","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNTA0MDE2Mw==","updated_at":"2017-05-30T23:46:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/305040163","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Yeah i see..\r\n\r\nRather than handle the layer on the Material, would an option be to have onBeforeRender and onAfterRender be called twice on the object once with each Left and Right Cameras?  ( Or may be have new onArrayCameraRender functions )\r\n\r\nThe main projectObject() layer test would be done on ArrayCamera and then the two Left and Right layer test would be called within the ArrayCamera render loop.\r\n\r\nThe main situation I have is needing to update a custom material ( and actually 2 render targets ) with some parameters generated from left and right camera matrices.  So to be able to get access to those matrices directly from an object would be handy. Otherwise i have to create two of the same object.\r\n","created_at":"2017-05-31T15:34:44.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11083#issuecomment-305225921","id":305225921,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11083","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNTIyNTkyMQ==","updated_at":"2017-05-31T15:34:44.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/305225921","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/248957?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/jamieowen","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0ODk1Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"jamieowen","type":"User","id":248957,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> would an option be to have onBeforeRender and onAfterRender be called twice on the object once with each Left and Right Cameras?\r\n\r\nNot sure that it's a good idea...\r\n\r\n> The main situation I have is needing to update a custom material ( and actually 2 render targets ) with some parameters generated from left and right camera matrices. So to be able to get access to those matrices directly from an object would be handy. Otherwise i have to create two of the same object.\r\n\r\nDo you mind detailing a little bit more your use case? Creating two objects doesn't sound like a bad idea to me.","created_at":"2017-06-02T18:55:30.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11083#issuecomment-305880568","id":305880568,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11083","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNTg4MDU2OA==","updated_at":"2017-06-02T18:55:30.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/305880568","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Yeah thats cool to use two objects I can always restructure things differently.\r\n\r\nHere's the logic \/ use case and thoughts on the onBeforeRender\/etc.\r\n\r\nRoughly like this :\r\n\r\n```\r\nclass NewMesh extends Mesh{\r\n\t\t\r\n\tconstructor(){\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tsuper( null,null );\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\tthis.leftEyeRTT = new WebGLRenderTarget();\r\n\t\tthis.rightEyeRTT = new WebGLRenderTarget();\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\/\/ Scene with some objects to render to render targets.\r\n\t\tthis.mixScene = new Scene(); \r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\/\/ Full screen quad\r\n\t\tthis.geometry = ...\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\/\/ A custom material that renders the RTTs with some additional requirements for\r\n\t\t\/\/ camera dependant uniforms.\r\n\t\tthis.material = new CustomMaterial( {\r\n\t\t\tuniforms: {\r\n\t\t\t\tmixTexture: { value: this.leftEyeRTT.texture },\r\n\t\t\t\tcamMatrixRelatedProp: { value: new Vector2() }\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t} );\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t}\r\n\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\/\/ Called before three.js render() on a custom first scene graph pass.\r\n\tpreRender( scene, camera, renderer ){\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tif( !camera.isArrayCamera ){ \/\/ No VR.\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\trenderer.render( this.mixScene, camera, this.leftEyeRTT );\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tthis.material.uniforms.mixTexture.value = this.leftEyeRTT.texture\r\n\t\t\tthis.material.uniforms.camMatrixRelatedProp.value = \/\/ generate for camera, etc...\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t}else{ \/\/ Yes VR\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\trenderer.render( this.mixScene, camera.cameras[0], this.leftEyeRTT );\r\n\t\t\trenderer.render( this.mixScene, camera.cameras[1], this.rightEyeRTT );\r\n\t\r\n\t\t\t\/\/ The uniforms cannot be set here as we don't know when we are about to draw with left or right cameras.\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\/\/ I think that it looks like mesh.onBeforeRender() is best place to set\r\n\t\t\t\/\/ uniforms in a one class setup but when they are camera dependent\r\n\t\t\t\/\/ there is no onBeforeRender VR equivalent. ( like onBeforeLeftEye, onBeforeRightEye )\r\n\t\t\t\/\/ ( Which kind of makes sense from an API point of view )\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\/\/ So you are sent down the two object route...\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t}\t\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd, more of a user related thing; if you were tempted to use the onBeforeRender() of a mesh in VR mode to render to a render texture using the renderer you would be breaking the state of the gl context which from what i understand is the main performance benefit of not switching materials\/etc during the left\/right render process.\r\n\r\nMay be there should be a separate onPreRender stage on an object3d that isn't so nested in the render process so it can't be abused!?\r\n","created_at":"2017-06-04T16:53:25.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11083#issuecomment-306052160","id":306052160,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11083","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNjA1MjE2MA==","updated_at":"2017-06-04T20:32:36.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/306052160","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/248957?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/jamieowen","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0ODk1Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"jamieowen","type":"User","id":248957,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jamieowen\/orgs"}}]}